Three people were killed and two othersinjured when a huge explosion, believed to be a bomb, went offin a suburb of Botswana's capital Gaborone.    Witnesses told Reuters the blast, near the headquarters ofthe Botswana Defence Force, occurred at about 2 A.M. (1200 GMT)and flattened several houses.    Minutes after the explosion Botswana soldiers sealed offthe scene, which is near where South African troops last Maylaunched a military attack against alleged guerrilla targets. Reuter&#3;